    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "48d3d051_8fbc27b8",
        "filename": "android/android-emu/android/ffmpeg-muxer.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 540,
      "author": {
        "id": 1082465
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-01-31T16:15:04Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Why 50 ms? Is it possible to have a 49 ms pause, not insert a silent buffer, and make Chrome desync by +49 ms every time you have a 49ms pause (until it becomes seconds)?\n\nAlso, does the insertion of of the silent buffer ever add any extra delay?\n If so, this is going to regress behavior on browsers where audio playback can deal with not having silent buffers.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 536,
        "startChar": 16,
        "endLine": 540,
        "endChar": 17
      },
      "revId": "01bd827b63ae342313c273253aa6fd418898d066",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "4f14478a_ade97480",
        "filename": "android/android-emu/android/ffmpeg-muxer.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 540,
      "author": {
        "id": 1128849
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-02-15T20:45:11Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This is more like a practical value. In theory, it should be 48000 * 4 bytes per second (with sampling rate of 48000 hz, 2 channels, 16-bit), which corresponds to 9600 bytes per 50 msec. Somehow, we actually inserted more than this value, we insert 4 * 4096 \u003d 16,384 bytes per 50 msec to make chrome to work well.\n\nYou are right about that 50 msec may cause delays if we get real audio while inserting silence. One thing to note the time to insert silent does not take 50 msec, it\u0027s instant, like a couple of msec, so it real audio arrives, the silence in queue may not fully save to the final video file. ffmpeg queues audio samples, and process them based on timestamp. My guess is if there are overlaps, the previous audio sample will get shortened.",
      "parentUuid": "48d3d051_8fbc27b8",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 536,
        "startChar": 16,
        "endLine": 540,
        "endChar": 17
      },
      "revId": "01bd827b63ae342313c273253aa6fd418898d066",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "3d5b75ef_bf59c954",
        "filename": "android/android-emu/android/ffmpeg-muxer.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 540,
      "author": {
        "id": 1082465
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-02-16T16:25:29Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\"One thing to note the time to insert silent does not take 50 msec, it\u0027s instant, like a couple of msec\"\n\nI\u0027m aware that the actual encoding of this packet shouldn\u0027t take 50 msec, but I think this doesn\u0027t address the concern I had about the 49ms problem. There\u0027s still the possibility of a 49 ms pause (in the real audio source, not encoding) causing a 49ms shift in time on Chrome anyway since silence will not be inserted, right?\n\nAlso, is the plan to submit this CL as is? What about when we talked about doing this in a separate pass over the video preview\u0027s audio track when the save button for that is clicked? Then that would let us insert exact silences in the finished audio track without having to worry about writing code that satisfies those kinds of couple-ms timing constraints.",
      "parentUuid": "4f14478a_ade97480",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 536,
        "startChar": 16,
        "endLine": 540,
        "endChar": 17
      },
      "revId": "01bd827b63ae342313c273253aa6fd418898d066",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": true
    },
